The PM will be making a Prime Ministerial statement on Afghanistan at 12:00 PM AEDT today. Watch it live here - http://t.co/7LnAF3eI TeamJG
PM: "Australia’s national interests in Afghanistan are unchanged - There must be no safe haven for terrorists in Afghanistan."
PM: "Working alongside the Afghan National Interdiction Unit, our Special Forces disrupt the narcotics trade."
PM: "Another example of our work in building Afghan security capacity is our work at the Afghan National Army Artillery Training School."
PM: "In Uruzgan Australians also work with the Afghan police to get them ready for transition."
PM: "Pakistan, its military and people, are on the frontline of terrorism and have been victims of its violence themselves."
PM: "It is time for Pakistan to do more to counter terrorism and extremism."
PM: "Over the next three years, Australia will complete our mission of training and transition. Australia will not abandon Afghanistan."
PM: "We know the good things we have done have come at a high cost. There have been days of sorrow and we do not forget."
PM: "We will defend our national interests. We will deny terrorism a safe haven in Afghanistan. We will complete our mission."

We remember today the united leadership of 1943 and the National Pact that put Lebanon above any foreign allegiances to the East or West
The conditions for Independence are freedom from foreign occupation and the extension of the state's authority over its entire territory
Economic growth, social equality and basic health and financial aid for citizens in need are also prerequisites for any independent state
For the first time since 1975, we have no external foreign forces on our lands, friend or enemy, and no internal conflicts for 3 years
We established diplomatic relations with Syria, passing the oil & gas law, are working on a just election law and one for regaining citizenship
We must respect the dialogue table's decisions regarding disarming palestinians and our commitment to the international tribunal
We must question through dialogue whether our problems lie within our constitution and laws or in their application and fix those gaps
We must encourage Lebanese expatriates to participate in our political life, and strengthen their bonds to their home country
We support all democratic reforms in the region and all arab causes, especially the Palestinian cause, while rejecting naturalization
I call on Lebanese to reject all that affects our national unity and their dreams of a better tomorrow negatively
